---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Predictable Software Delivery" fullWidth>

  <!-- DARK HERO -->
  <div class="hero-unified">
    <div class="hero-dark">
      <div class="wide-wrap">
        <div class="hero-chip">
          <span class="hero-chip-dot"></span>
          <span>95% forecast accuracy across all engagements</span>
        </div>
        <h1>Predictable Software<br>Delivery for Leaders<br>Who Can't Afford to <em>Miss</em></h1>
        <p class="hero-subtext">NolteOS turns 20 years of delivery data into predictable, fixed-price software delivery. Describe what you're building and get a delivery plan with 95% accuracy on scope, timeline, and cost.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="btn-hero btn-hero-primary" href="https://os.nolte.io">Get Your Delivery Plan</a>
          <a class="btn-hero btn-hero-secondary" href="https://nolte.io/the-predictability-gap">Read The Predictability Gap</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PILLARS -->
    <div class="pillars">
      <div class="pillars-grid">
        <div class="pillar">
          <span class="feature-label">Delivery</span>
          <h3>Guaranteed Delivery</h3>
          <p>Fixed price per delivery. You only pay for what we ship. Our incentives are structurally aligned with yours.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <span class="feature-label">Accuracy</span>
          <h3>95% Prediction Accuracy</h3>
          <p>NolteOS uses three years of flow data to forecast delivery. No estimates, no guesswork, no surprises.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <span class="feature-label">Experience</span>
          <h3>Founders Who've Exited</h3>
          <p>We've built companies from zero, scaled them, and sold them. That experience shapes every decision we make.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar">
          <span class="feature-label">Model</span>
          <h3>Efficiency Over Activity</h3>
          <p>We measure outcomes delivered, not hours billed. When your interests come first, speed becomes profitable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TRUST LOGOS -->
    <div class="trust-bar">
      <p class="trust-label">Trusted by teams shipping critical software</p>
      <div class="trust-logos">
        <span class="brand-logo brand-hbo">HBO</span>
        <span class="brand-logo brand-bloomscape">Bloomscape</span>
        <span class="brand-logo brand-barrys">Barry's</span>
        <span class="brand-logo brand-odie">Odie</span>
        <span class="brand-logo brand-amtrak">Amtrak</span>
        <span class="brand-logo brand-petplate">PetPlate</span>
        <span class="brand-logo brand-wake">Wake</span>
        <span class="brand-logo brand-footprint">Footprint</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HUMAN: WHO WE ARE -->
  <div class="human-section">
    <div class="human-inner">
      <span class="human-eyebrow">Our Team</span>
      <div class="human-photo-wide">
        <div class="human-photo-placeholder">Team photo coming soon</div>
        <span class="human-caption">Nolte team — Americas</span>
      </div>
      <div class="human-text-row">
        <div class="human-text-left">
          <h2>We've been in your seat</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="human-text-right">
          <p>Nolte was founded by operators who've built companies from zero, scaled them, and sold them. We know what it feels like to approve a six-figure software engagement and hope it works out. That's why we built a system that removes hope from the equation.</p>
          <p class="human-text-secondary">We're a distributed team across the Americas — designers, engineers, and product strategists who measure success by what ships, not what's billed.</p>
          <a class="human-link" href="/about">Learn about our story &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STATS + FEATURED ARTICLE -->
  <div class="stats-featured-unified">
    <div class="stats-featured-inner">
      <span class="stats-eyebrow">By the Numbers</span>
      <div class="stats-row-dark">
        <div class="stat-dark">
          <div class="stat-value">95<span class="stat-accent">%</span></div>
          <div class="stat-label">Forecast accuracy</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-dark">
          <div class="stat-value">20<span class="stat-accent">yrs</span></div>
          <div class="stat-label">Delivering software</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-dark">
          <div class="stat-value">75<span class="stat-accent">/mo</span></div>
          <div class="stat-label">Deliveries shipped</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-dark">
          <div class="stat-value">0<span class="stat-accent"> hrs</span></div>
          <div class="stat-label">Billed per hour</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="featured-dark">
        <div class="featured-dark-text">
          <span class="featured-tag">Featured Article</span>
          <h2>The Predictability Gap</h2>
          <p>Every business function forecasts in order to be predictable. Software development does neither. It's the only function on the P&L where leadership approves spend without knowing what will be delivered, when, or what it will cost.</p>
          <p>AI didn't close this gap. It made it wider. In industries where compliance deadlines, patient safety, and regulatory obligations are non-negotiable, the gap isn't inefficiency. It's exposure.</p>
          <a class="featured-link" href="https://nolte.io/the-predictability-gap">Read the full article by Jeffrey Nolte &rarr;</a>
        </div>
        <div class="featured-dark-quote">
          <span class="featured-quote-label">From the Article</span>
          <blockquote>AI didn't close this gap. It made it wider. In industries where compliance deadlines, patient safety, and regulatory obligations are non-negotiable, the gap isn't inefficiency. It's exposure.</blockquote>
          <span class="featured-quote-author">— Jeffrey Nolte, Founder</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
  <div class="how-it-works">
    <div class="wide-wrap">
      <span class="how-eyebrow">The process</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">How Predictive Delivery Works</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">Three steps. One forecast. Zero surprises.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="steps-grid">
      <div class="step-cell step-cell--situation">
        <span class="step-num-inline step-num--situation">01</span>
        <h3>Situation</h3>
        <span class="step-subtitle">Describe what you're building</span>
        <p>Tell us what you need. We break it into discrete, measurable deliveries, each with a clear definition of done. For regulated products, compliance requirements are scoped as deliveries from day one.</p>
        <div class="step-visual step-visual--situation">
          <span class="sv-key">Input</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">Describe your product</span><br>
          <span class="sv-key">Output</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">Scoped deliveries</span><br>
          <span class="sv-key">Each</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">Definition of done</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-cell step-cell--assessment">
        <span class="step-num-inline step-num--assessment">02</span>
        <h3>Assessment</h3>
        <span class="step-subtitle">NolteOS forecasts your build</span>
        <p>Our delivery operating system uses three years of flow data to predict exactly when each delivery lands, what it costs, and what the total engagement looks like.</p>
        <div class="step-visual step-visual--assessment">
          <span class="sv-key">Accuracy</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val sv-val--highlight" id="accuracy-counter">95.2%</span><br>
          <span class="sv-key">Timeline</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">Week 8</span><br>
          <span class="sv-key">Model</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">Pay per delivery</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-cell step-cell--plan">
        <span class="step-num-inline step-num--plan">03</span>
        <h3>Plan</h3>
        <span class="step-subtitle">Get your delivery plan</span>
        <p>You receive a complete delivery plan: what gets built, in what order, when it ships, and what it costs. Fixed price per delivery. You pay for what ships, nothing more.</p>
        <div class="step-visual step-visual--plan">
          <span class="sv-key">Scope</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">Guaranteed</span><br>
          <span class="sv-key">Price</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">Fixed per delivery</span><br>
          <span class="sv-key">Risk</span> &rarr; <span class="sv-val">We carry it</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="steps-cta-wrap">
      <a class="btn-accent" href="https://insights.nolte.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Get your delivery plan</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    (function () {
      var el = document.getElementById('accuracy-counter');
      if (!el) return;
      var fired = false;
      var observer = new IntersectionObserver(function (entries) {
        if (entries[0].isIntersecting && !fired) {
          fired = true;
          observer.disconnect();
          var target = 95.2;
          var duration = 1200;
          var start = performance.now();
          function tick(now) {
            var t = Math.min((now - start) / duration, 1);
            var ease = 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3);
            var val = (target * ease).toFixed(1);
            el.textContent = val + '%';
            if (t < 1) requestAnimationFrame(tick);
          }
          el.textContent = '0.0%';
          requestAnimationFrame(tick);
        }
      }, { threshold: 0.3 });
      observer.observe(el);
    })();
  </script>

  <!-- NOLTEOS CALLOUT -->
  <div class="nolteos-callout">
    <div class="nolteos-callout-inner">
      <div class="nolteos-callout-content">
        <div class="hero-chip hero-chip--dark"><span class="hero-chip-dot"></span><span>NolteOS</span></div>
        <h2>The predictability engine behind every delivery</h2>
        <p>NolteOS uses 20 years of delivery data to forecast scope, timeline, and cost before work begins. It's how we price per delivery, not per hour — and how our clients know exactly what they're getting before they commit.</p>
        <div class="snapshot-features callout-features">
          <div class="snapshot-feature" data-highlight="callout-accuracy">
            <span class="snapshot-feature-dot"></span>
            <div>
              <strong class="snapshot-feature-name">95% forecast accuracy across all engagements</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="snapshot-feature" data-highlight="callout-tracking">
            <span class="snapshot-feature-dot"></span>
            <div>
              <strong class="snapshot-feature-name">Real-time delivery tracking and metrics</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="snapshot-feature" data-highlight="callout-visibility">
            <span class="snapshot-feature-dot"></span>
            <div>
              <strong class="snapshot-feature-name">Transparent scope, timeline, and cost visibility</strong>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <a class="nolteos-callout-link" href="/about/nolteos">See how NolteOS works &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="nolteos-callout-preview">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1rem; display: block;">The Predictability Engine</span>
        <div class="shot-window shot-window-dark">
          <div class="shot-toolbar">
            <span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span><span class="shot-dot"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="shot-content">
            <div class="nolteos-mini-metrics">
              <div class="nolteos-mini-metric" data-zone="callout-accuracy" data-label="Accuracy">
                <span class="nolteos-mini-label">Forecast Accuracy</span>
                <span class="nolteos-mini-value">95.2%</span>
              </div>
              <div class="nolteos-mini-metric" data-zone="callout-tracking">
                <span class="nolteos-mini-label">Cycle Time</span>
                <span class="nolteos-mini-value">4.8d</span>
              </div>
              <div class="nolteos-mini-metric" data-zone="callout-tracking" data-label="Tracking">
                <span class="nolteos-mini-label">Weekly Throughput</span>
                <span class="nolteos-mini-value">18</span>
              </div>
              <div class="nolteos-mini-metric" data-zone="callout-visibility" data-label="Visibility">
                <span class="nolteos-mini-label">On-Time Rate</span>
                <span class="nolteos-mini-value">97%</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script>
    (function () {
      var section = document.querySelector('.nolteos-callout');
      if (!section) return;
      var features = section.querySelectorAll('.snapshot-feature[data-highlight]');
      if (!features.length) return;

      // Set first as active
      features[0].classList.add('is-active');
      document.querySelectorAll('[data-zone="' + features[0].dataset.highlight + '"]')
        .forEach(function (z) { z.classList.add('is-highlighted'); });

      features.forEach(function (feature) {
        var zones = document.querySelectorAll('[data-zone="' + feature.dataset.highlight + '"]');

        feature.addEventListener('mouseenter', function () {
          features.forEach(function (sib) {
            sib.classList.remove('is-active');
            document.querySelectorAll('[data-zone="' + sib.dataset.highlight + '"]')
              .forEach(function (z) { z.classList.remove('is-highlighted'); });
          });
          feature.classList.add('is-active');
          zones.forEach(function (z) { z.classList.add('is-highlighted'); });
        });

        feature.addEventListener('mouseleave', function () {
          feature.classList.remove('is-active');
          zones.forEach(function (z) { z.classList.remove('is-highlighted'); });
          features[0].classList.add('is-active');
          document.querySelectorAll('[data-zone="' + features[0].dataset.highlight + '"]')
            .forEach(function (z) { z.classList.add('is-highlighted'); });
        });
      });
    })();
  </script>

  <!-- CASE STUDIES -->
  <div class="case-studies">
    <div class="case-header">
      <div class="case-header-left">
        <span class="case-eyebrow">Our work</span>
        <h2 class="section-heading">Delivery across <em>regulated industries</em></h2>
